# Portfolio — Project Context

Single-page static site merging About, Toolkit, and Contact. All UI lives in one HTML shell; behavior and styles are split by concern.

## Directory structure

```
portfolio/
├── .cursorfile           # This file — project rules & layout
├── index.html            # Shell: head, header, footer, three view sections
├── songs.txt             # Spotify embed URLs (one per line) for shuffle player
├── css/
│   └── style.css         # Custom CSS (scrollbar, toolkit logo hovers, form extras)
└── js/
    ├── theme-init.js     # Sync in <head> — apply saved theme before paint
    ├── tailwind-config.js
    ├── navigation.js     # SPA views + mobile menu + nav active state
    ├── theme.js          # Theme toggle button
    ├── spotify.js        # Spotify iframe shuffle
    └── contact.js        # Web3Forms contact submission
```

## Views (client-side routing)

| View     | Hash        | Source (legacy)   |
|----------|-------------|-------------------|
| About    | `#` / empty | `../index.html`   |
| Toolkit  | `#toolkit`  | `../toolkit.html` |
| Contact  | `#contact`  | `../contact.html` |

Navigation uses `data-nav="about|toolkit|contact"` on header links — do not use separate HTML files for these sections.

## Conventions

- **Tailwind**: CDN with `forms`, `container-queries`, `typography`. Config in `js/tailwind-config.js`. Base `@layer` rules stay in `index.html` as `<style type="text/tailwindcss">` (Tailwind must process them).
- **No inline scripts** in `index.html` except AdSense if required — use `js/*.js`.
- **Paths**: Always relative to `portfolio/` (`css/`, `js/`, `songs.txt`).
- **Theme**: `localStorage.theme` = `light` | `dark`. Init in `theme-init.js`, toggle in `theme.js`.
- **Blog**: External link only (`/blog`) — not part of this SPA.
- **Semantic HTML**: `<header>`, `<main>`, `<footer>`, `<section>` per view.
- **Minimal diffs**: When editing one view, touch only its section in `index.html` plus shared assets if needed.

## Adding a new view

1. Add `<section id="view-{name}" class="page-view hidden">` in `index.html`.
2. Register `{name}` in `VIEWS` array in `js/navigation.js`.
3. Add nav link with `data-nav="{name}"` in header (desktop + mobile).

## External dependencies

- Tailwind CDN, Google Fonts (Inter, Lora, Playfair Display, JetBrains Mono), Material Symbols
- Web3Forms API (`contact.js`)
- Spotify embed iframes (`songs.txt`)
